<F P=103> EA1804182594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura </F>
<F P=105>  Kinyarwanda </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Kigali, the fighting continues. The Rwandan 
Patriotic Front [RPF] combatants are still holding all the 
positions they captured. Mutara region is under the control of 
the RPF combatants. The government troops never returned there. 
In the Byumba area, the RPF troops are doing very well. 
Contrary to lies that have been spread, Byumba town is entirely 
in the hands of the RPF troops. In Ruhengeri, the RPF 
combatants control many areas of the prefecture while the 
government troops are tired and have started fleeing. They have 
now resorted to seeking help from the Interahamwe [Republican 
National Movement for Democracy and Development militias] and 
Coalition for the Defense of the Republic members, involving 
them in a war they know very well that they will never win. 

</TEXT>

