<H3> <TI>   New Justice Minister Urges Fighters To Turn in Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Justice Minister Urges Fighters To Turn in Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2104103094 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 21 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2104103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Monrovia Radio ELBC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Liberia's new justice minister, Councillor Laveli 
Supuwood, has called on fighters to turn in their arms and work 
toward enhancing the peace process. Minister Supuwood was 
speaking yesterday at the Executive Mansion following the 
commissioning of he and three other NPFL [National Patriotic 
Front of Liberia] nominees confirmed yesterday by the 
Transitional Assembly. He said Liberians should not be deprived 
of their peace and freedom of movement only to satisfy a handful 
of people. Minister Supuwood also called on the international 
community, friendly governments, and the business community to 
recognize the Liberian National Transitional Government, saying 
it is the legitimate government of the people of Liberia. 

</TEXT>

