  [Text] The Swazi police have shed some light on rumors that 
South African right-wingers are undergoing military training in 
the Lufufa Mountains of north-western Swaziland. A police 
spokesman said locals in the remote area could have mistaken 
South African policemen conducting a joint air and ground 
anti-dagga operation in February for a foreign military force. 
