<DOCNO> FBIS4-936 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drafr076_c_94021" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-AFR-94-076 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PAC Applies To Join Transitional Executive Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PAC Applies To Join Transitional Executive Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1904162894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1559 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1904162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria April 19 SAPA -- The Pan Africanist 
Congress [PAC] has applied to join the Transitional Executive 
Council [TEC]. The move, in the second last week of the TEC's 
existence, would allow soldiers of the PAC's armed wing, the 
Azanian Peoples Liberation Army, to join the National 
Peacekeeping Force. 

</TEXT>

