<F P=103> MB2004094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Department of Home Affairs says fewer than 
500,000 people are still without identity documents or voter's 
cards. The department says in a statement issued in Pretoria 
that more than 22 million potential voters are now in possession 
of the necessary documents. Thousands of identity documents 
have accumulated at the department's regional and district 
offices and applicants have been urged to collect them. 

