<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government, Renamo Generals Sign Future Army Accords </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government, Renamo Generals Sign Future Army Accords </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1604105194 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0800 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1604105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Four accords concerning the creation of the new 
Mozambique Defense Armed Forces, FADM, were signed in Maputo 
yesterday by General Tobias Dai, on behalf of the government, 
and General Edmundo de Morais, of the Mozambique National 
Resistance. 
  Those documents dealt with hierarchical structure, general 
organization, and the organization and training of the battalion 
of special forces and of air force personnel. 
  Aldo Ajello, head of the UN Operations in Mozambique, said 
that the signing of those documents is a step forward toward 
pacifying the country. 

</TEXT>

