<H3> <TI>   Inkatha Freedom Party To Participate in Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Inkatha Freedom Party To Participate in Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Parliament To Meet 25 Apr </H4>

<F P=102> MB1904143094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1400 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1904143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Dirk van Zyl] </F>
  [Text] Cape Town April 19 SAPA -- Parliament is to sit on 
Monday [25 April] to consider legislative amendments flowing 
from the agreement bringing the Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] into 
the elections. This was confirmed on Tuesday afternoon by the 
parliamentary secretariat. 

</TEXT>

