<H3> <TI>   EU Grants 20.5 Million Rands </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Grants 20.5 Million Rands </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1504153894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1504153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The European Union, EU, has presented 20.5 million 
rands to the Independent Electoral Commission [IEC]. The head 
of the union's delegation in South Africa, Mr. Erwan Fouere, 
handed the money to the chairman of the IEC, Mr. Justice Johan 
Kriegler, at a ceremony in Johannesburg this morning. Mr. 
Fouere said the donation was proof of the union's commitment to 
transition in South Africa, and its confidence in democracy. 
Just over half of the money will be used for specific 
educational programs. The rest of the money will go to the 
IEC's election fund and will be allocated to parties taking part 
in the election. 

</TEXT>

