<H4>    Hostel Cordoned Off </H4>

<F P=102> MB1804210394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1951 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1804210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg April 18 SAPA -- Security forces have 
cordoned off Thokoza hostel following the Monday [18 April] 
morning gunbattle between hostel inmates and National 
Peacekeeping Force [NPKF] troops, SABC TV news reports. News 
photographer Ken Oosterbroek was caught in the conflict and died 
before he could receive treatment. Two of his colleagues were 
injured. 
  NPKF spokesman Col Connie van Rensburg said the situation 
was 
still tense on Monday night. 

</TEXT>

