<H4>    Tutu Calls For SADF To Return </H4>

<F P=102> MB1904122194 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1205 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1904122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg April 19 SAPA -- The decision to 
withdraw South African Defence Force [SADF] troops from Thokoza 
on the East Rand "was not working", Archbishop Desmond Tutu said 
in a statement on Tuesday. Archbishop Tutu said the conflict in 
Thokoza had been brought under control by the SADF in recent 
months, but it had again intensified since the withdrawal to the 
point when 19 people had died violently since the weekend. 
  The church, said Archbishop Tutu, had supported the 
formation 
of the National Peacekeeping Force [NPKF], but the NPKF was 
being asked to do an impossible job. 
  "Reports from church members indicate there is a strong 
desire that the SADF should return and we call on the 
Transitional Executive Council as a matter of urgency to send 
the soldiers back." 

</TEXT>

