<H3> <TI>   SADF To Produce Program To `Communicate' With Public </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SADF To Produce Program To `Communicate' With Public </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1604074994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 2126 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB1604074994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria April 15 SAPA -- The South African Defence 
Force [SADF] will soon host a one-hour programme on Radio 2000 
to communicate with the public, especially the SADF's part-time 
forces. A statement issued on Friday [15 April] on behalf of the 
SADF by chief director of communication Maj-Gen John Rolt said 
the programme, tentatively scheduled for Wednesday evenings, 
would be first aired within a fortnight, pending finalisation of 
an agreement with the South African Broadcasting Corporation. 
  The statement also said a newspaper and radio advertising 
campaign was in the offing to improve the image of the SADF and 
create a climate favourable to the establishment of a new 
National Defence Force on April 27. Empahasis would be placed on 
communicating with the black community. 
  Four full-page advertisements would be placed 11 times each, 
and 27-second radio spots would be aired 500 times. 

</TEXT>

