<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Afrikaner Groups Deny Military Training in Swaziland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Afrikaner Groups Deny Military Training in Swaziland </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB1804121394 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB1804121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The national media spokesman for the Afrikaner 
Volksfront [National Front -- AVF), Mr. Koos Kemp, has denied 
allegations that soldiers from the AVF are undergoing training 
in northern Swaziland. Earlier a tribal chief said he had 
handed information about the alleged training to the Swazi 
defense force. Mr. Kemp also denied having any knowledge of a 
huge meeting allegedly held by the AVF in the Lubodlwana region 
of Swaziland last week. 
  The leader of the AWB [Afrikaner Resistance Movement], Mr. 
Eugene Terreblanche, has also denied knowledge of right-wing 
troops being trained in Swaziland. He was not prepared to 
comment on whether the AWB was involved in the training of any 
other groups. However, he did confirm that training of his own 
commandos had been stepped up. 

</TEXT>

