<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   IEC Rules Out Another Party Joining Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IEC Rules Out Another Party Joining Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2104193094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2104193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] has ruled 
out the possibility of another party joining the election. The 
chairman of the IEC, Mr. Justice Johann Kriegler, said in 
Johannesburg that if the CP [Conservative Party] reached an 
agreement on entering the election, the IEC would be prepared to 
count votes for the Freedom Front separately in some areas. An 
IEC spokesman added that by four o'clock this afternoon the IFP 
[Inkatha Freedom Party] had still not submitted its candidates 
lists. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

