<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Commission Denies Numbering Ballots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electoral Commission Denies Numbering Ballots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2004183494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2004183494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Independent Electoral Commission [IEC] has 
denied that the ballot papers for the elections next week will 
be numbered. The IEC said in a statement that the counterfoil of 
the ballot paper had a serial number, but that there was no mark 
on the ballot paper itself. It said that no inscription would 
be made on the counterfoil by an electoral officer. The voter 
would have his knuckles sprayed with invisible ink, and his 
document marked with invisible ink to control voting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

